> [!CAUTION]
> **Severity: High** — 4 of 6 tests in this file assert only `response.Should().NotBeNull()`, which will **never fail**. These tests give false confidence.

| Test | Problem |
|------|---------|
| `should_return_success_when_get_users_page_authenticated` | Asserts `NotBeNull` instead of `200 OK` |
| `should_contain_table_element_when_get_users_page` | Asserts `NotBeNull` instead of parsing HTML |
| `should_display_user_data_when_users_exist` | Seeds data but never checks the response body |
