### C3. Inconsistent Lifecycle Management: `IClassFixture` vs `IDisposable`

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Severity: High** — Two test classes use `IClassFixture<CustomWebApplicationFactory>` (shared factory across all tests in the class), while 12 use `IDisposable` (new factory per test). This creates **data leakage** risk in the fixture classes.

| Pattern | Classes |
|---------|---------|
| `IClassFixture` (shared) | `ErrorIndexIntegrationTests`, `UsersIndexIntegrationTests` |
| `IDisposable` (isolated) | All other 12 classes |

The shared-factory tests (`UsersIndexIntegrationTests`) share the same InMemory database across all tests in that class. The `should_display_user_data_when_users_exist` test seeds "testuser123" but this data **leaks into every other test** in the class. Since `AllowAutoRedirect = false` is set at the class level in `UsersIndexIntegrationTests`, the first test checks for a redirect — this will pass. But if test execution order changes, results could become non-deterministic.

**Recommendation:** Standardise on `IDisposable` with per-test factories for full isolation, matching the majority pattern.

