### M2. `TestAuthHandler` Generates New `NameIdentifier` Per Request

[TestAuthHandler.cs:24](file:///Users/colmkenna/Source/IdentityServerStarter/Tests/Integration/IdentityServerAspNetIdentity.IntegrationTests/Infrastructure/TestAuthHandler.cs#L24): `Guid.NewGuid().ToString()` is called in `HandleAuthenticateAsync`, so every request gets a **different user ID**. This means:
- You can never look up the "authenticated user" in the database
- Any page that uses `User.FindFirst(ClaimTypes.NameIdentifier)` sees a different user each time

If current tests don't depend on user-ID consistency, this works. But it becomes a trap if future tests need it. Consider using a **stable** test user ID.

