### M7. `SendFormAsync` Sets Values Twice

In [HttpClientExtensions.cs](file:///Users/colmkenna/Source/IdentityServerStarter/Tests/Integration/IdentityServerAspNetIdentity.IntegrationTests/Infrastructure/HttpClientExtensions.cs#L29-L44), `formValues` are applied to the DOM elements (lines 29–44) **and** later added as form-encoded content (lines 103–108). The DOM manipulation on lines 29–44 is effectively dead code for POST requests since the form data is rebuilt from scratch on line 66. This could lead to confusion about which path applies.

