## Minor Issues / Suggestions

### S1. Naming Convention Inconsistencies

| Style | Examples |
|-------|---------|
| `PascalCase_Underscores` (majority) | `Get_AdminIndex_Returns200`, `PostEdit_ValidInput_Returns302` |
| `snake_case` | `should_return_success_status_when_get_error_page`, `should_redirect_to_login_when...` |

The `ErrorIndexIntegrationTests` and `UsersIndexIntegrationTests` use `should_*` snake_case, while all others use PascalCase with underscores. Pick one convention.

