### S2. Redundant `using` Directives

Several test files import namespaces that are already in `GlobalUsings.cs`:
- `using System.Net;` — in [AdminIndexIntegrationTests.cs:1](file:///Users/colmkenna/Source/IdentityServerStarter/Tests/Integration/IdentityServerAspNetIdentity.IntegrationTests/Pages/AdminIndexIntegrationTests.cs#L1), [ApiScopesCreateIntegrationTests.cs:1](file:///Users/colmkenna/Source/IdentityServerStarter/Tests/Integration/IdentityServerAspNetIdentity.IntegrationTests/Pages/ApiScopesCreateIntegrationTests.cs#L1), and most others
- `using FluentAssertions;` — in [ClientsEditIntegrationTests.cs:4](file:///Users/colmkenna/Source/IdentityServerStarter/Tests/Integration/IdentityServerAspNetIdentity.IntegrationTests/Pages/ClientsEditIntegrationTests.cs#L4)
- `using Microsoft.Extensions.DependencyInjection;` — in several files

Not harmful but adds noise. Can be cleaned up.

