### S4. Empty `<Folder>` Entry in `.csproj`

```xml
<ItemGroup>
    <Folder Include="Pages\" />
</ItemGroup>
```

This is a Visual Studio artifact with no effect. Can be removed.

---

### S5. No Test Collection Parallelisation

`xunit.runner.json` disables **all** parallelism. Given that each test creates its own `CustomWebApplicationFactory` with a unique InMemory database name (`Guid.NewGuid()`), most tests **could** run in parallel safely. Consider enabling `parallelizeTestCollections: true` for faster CI runs — but first fix the `IClassFixture` tests (C3) which could interfere.

---

### S6. Missing `GC.SuppressFinalize` in `Dispose`

The 12 classes implementing `IDisposable` don't call `GC.SuppressFinalize(this)`. While this is a minor code-analysis warning for test classes (no finalizer exists), adding it would suppress CA1816 if you enable analyzers.

---

### S7. Antiforgery Globally Disabled But `AntiforgeryTokenHelper` Exists

[CustomWebApplicationFactory.cs:99–102](file:///Users/colmkenna/Source/IdentityServerStarter/Tests/Integration/IdentityServerAspNetIdentity.IntegrationTests/Infrastructure/CustomWebApplicationFactory.cs#L99-L102) adds `IgnoreAntiforgeryTokenAttribute` globally, so antiforgery is never validated. Yet `AntiforgeryTokenHelper` exists with full token generation logic. This helper is **unused** — either it's premature infrastructure or was left from a removed feature.

